<figureCitation id="9F8704DEFF86FF91BBE6F8AD0A60FA64" box="[721,822,1411,1433]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="20.[145,223,1878,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-282@20.[303,1266,891,1838]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 15. Caenocentron galesus, male genitalia A, lateral; B, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461374" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461374/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">Figs 15A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9F8704DEFF86FF91BA75F8AD0A39FA65" box="[834,879,1411,1432]" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="24.[145,225,1440,1462]" captionTargetBox="[148,757,196,1399]" captionTargetId="figure-536@24.[147,758,195,1400]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 19. Caenocentron pallas. A, wing venation. Male genitalia: B, lateral; C, dorsal; D, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461382" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461382/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">19B</figureCitation>
).......................................................................... 8
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="BC4800FEFF86FF91B988F88F0CD1F9EE" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
<paragraph id="0703185BFF86FF91B988F88F0CD1FA28" blockId="13.[191,1416,982,1862]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
<keyLead id="BC4DBB6EFF86FF91B988F88F0CD1FA28" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
6(5) Coxopodite, in ventral view, inner margin with brush of long setae and a pair of long sublateral stout spines; harpago basal third strongly enlarged (
<figureCitation id="9F8704DEFF86FF91BA25F8EE0A26FA28" box="[786,880,1472,1494]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="22.[810,888,1390,1412]" captionTargetBox="[812,1421,196,1349]" captionTargetId="figure-422@22.[811,1422,195,1350]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figure 17. Caenocentron immaculatum, male genitalia: A, lateral; B, dorsal; C, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461378/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">Fig. 17A</figureCitation>
)................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="C0BC63D8FF86FF91BDFEF8EF0CD1FA28" authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1991" box="[1225,1415,1472,1494]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Cnodocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immaculatum">
<emphasis id="35C8C449FF86FF91BDFEF8EF0CD1FA28" box="[1225,1415,1472,1494]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">C. immaculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0703185BFF86FF91B988F8F10CD1F9EE" blockId="13.[191,1416,982,1862]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
<keyLead id="BC4DBB6EFF86FF91B988F8F10CD1F9EE" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
6(5)’ Coxopodite, in ventral view, inner margin with brush of long setae, without any long stout spines; harpago basal third slightly enlarged or not enlarged (
<figureCitation id="9F8704DEFF86FF91BA59F8D00A98F9EE" box="[878,974,1534,1556]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="23.[163,241,1837,1859]" captionTargetBox="[166,775,1129,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-603@23.[165,776,1128,1798]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figure 18. Caenocentron lausus, male genitalia: A, lateral; B, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461380/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
) ............................................................ 7
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="BC4800FEFF86FF91B988FB320CD1F970" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
<paragraph id="0703185BFF86FF91B988FB320CD1F9AD" blockId="13.[191,1416,982,1862]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
<keyLead id="BC4DBB6EFF86FF91B988FB320CD1F9AD" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
7(6) Harpago base with a linear setal brush; coxopodite apical margin projection broad until the apex, bearing a short spine on ventroapical margin (
<figureCitation id="9F8704DEFF86FF91BA3FFB150A31F9AD" box="[776,871,1595,1617]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="23.[163,241,1837,1859]" captionTargetBox="[166,775,1129,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-603@23.[165,776,1128,1798]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figure 18. Caenocentron lausus, male genitalia: A, lateral; B, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461380/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
) .............................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="C0BC63D8FF86FF91BC28FB150CD1F9AD" authorityName=", Schmid" authorityYear="1982" box="[1311,1415,1595,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Cnodocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lausus">
<emphasis id="35C8C449FF86FF91BC28FB150CD1F9AD" box="[1311,1415,1595,1616]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">C. lausus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0703185BFF86FF91B988FB740CD1F970" blockId="13.[191,1416,982,1862]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
<keyLead id="BC4DBB6EFF86FF91B988FB740CD1F970" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
7(6)’ Harpago base without any setal brush; coxopodite apical margin projection tapering to a rounded apex, bearing a short spine subapically (
<figureCitation id="9F8704DEFF86FF91BBB2FB560B83F970" box="[645,725,1656,1678]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="15.[163,241,1499,1521]" captionTargetBox="[402,1203,196,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-157@15.[401,1204,195,1460]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 8. Caenocentron carlosdelarosai sp. nov. male genitalia. A, lateral; B, dorsal; C, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461364" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461364/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
) ..................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="C0BC63D8FF86FF91BD8AFB570CD1F970" authorityName="Vilarino &amp; Dias &amp; Bispo" authorityYear="2022" box="[1213,1415,1656,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Caenocentron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carlosdelarosai">
<emphasis id="35C8C449FF86FF91BD8AFB570CD1F970" box="[1213,1415,1656,1678]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">C. carlosdelarosai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="BC4800FEFF86FF91B988FBB90CDEF8B8" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
<paragraph id="0703185BFF86FF91B988FBB90CD1F914" blockId="13.[191,1416,982,1862]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
<keyLead id="BC4DBB6EFF86FF91B988FBB90CD1F914" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
8(5) Inferior appendage presenting a lobe covered with brush of setae near harpago base; coxopodite median region with almost indiscernible small setules; paraproct dorsal margin without process, ventroapical margin rounded (
<figureCitation id="9F8704DEFF86FF91B8F2FBFA0B17F914" box="[453,577,1748,1770]" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="24.[145,225,1440,1462]" captionTargetBox="[148,757,196,1399]" captionTargetId="figure-536@24.[147,758,195,1400]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 19. Caenocentron pallas. A, wing venation. Male genitalia: B, lateral; C, dorsal; D, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461382" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461382/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">Fig. 19B, C</figureCitation>
) .......................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="C0BC63D8FF86FF91BC13FBFB0CD1F914" authorityName="Schmid" authorityYear="1982" box="[1316,1415,1748,1770]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Cnodocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallas">
<emphasis id="35C8C449FF86FF91BC13FBFB0CD1F914" box="[1316,1415,1748,1770]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">C. pallas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0703185BFF86FF91B988FBDD0CDEF8B8" blockId="13.[191,1416,982,1862]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
<keyLead id="BC4DBB6EFF86FF91B988FBDD0CDEF8B8" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">
8(5)’ Inferior appendage without any brush of setae near harpago base; coxopodite median region with a transverse patch of setae; paraproct dorsal margin with short acute process, ventroapical margin acute (
<figureCitation id="9F8704DEFF86FF91B83CFA1E083CF8BB" box="[267,362,1840,1862]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="20.[145,223,1878,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-282@20.[303,1266,891,1838]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 15. Caenocentron galesus, male genitalia A, lateral; B, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461374" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461374/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354">Fig. 15A</figureCitation>
) ....................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="C0BC63D8FF86FF91BC21FA1F0CDEF8B8" authorityName="Schmid" authorityYear="1982" box="[1302,1416,1840,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Cnodocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galesus">C. galesus</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
